MENTAL delta. The elements accelerate away from the cursor and fly off screen!\n\nBut wait — for single element drag, it uses `moveElementTo` which sets ABSOLUTE position:\n```\nmoveElementTo(dragState.draggedElementId, {\n  x: dragState.startElementPosition.x + deltaX,\n  y: dragState.startElementPosition.y + deltaY,\n});\n```\n\nThis is correct — it sets absolute position = start + delta.\n\nBut for multi-select, it uses `moveSelectedElements({ dx: deltaX, dy: deltaY })` which does `position += delta`. This is WRONG because deltaX is the total delta from start, not incremental.\n\nSo the bug is:\n1. selectElement doesn't clear previous selection → multiple elements get selected\n2. moveSelectedElements applies total delta as incremental → elements fly off screen\n\nThe fix is TWO things:\n1. In handleElementMouseDown, clear selection before selecting new element (unless Shift is held)\n2. Fix moveSelectedElements to use absolute positioning or incremental deltas\n\nActually, the simplest fix: in handleElementMouseDown, when clicking a new element without Shift, clear selection first. This prevents the multi-select path from being triggered accidentally.",
