nipulates the `custom-elements-layer`.\n\nThe CHILDLIST mutations on `custom-elements-layer` during React renders suggest `CanvasElementRenderer`'s useEffect IS running during drag interactions. This could be because:\n- `renderVersion` changes (incremented in DiagramDisplay's renderResult useEffect)\n- `selectedElementIds` changes\n- `elements` reference changes (even if content is same)\n- Some other dependency triggers re-render\n\n### Key Files for This Bug\n- `src/components/canvas/DiagramDisplay.tsx` — renderResult useEffect wipes container and recreates SVG (lines ~125-270)\n- `src/components/canvas/CanvasElementRenderer.tsx` — useEffect syncs Redux elements to DOM (lines ~50-135)\n- `src/components/canvas/CanvasElementInteractions.tsx` — also queries `custom-elements-layer` (line 55)\n- `src/components/canvas/placement/useElementPlacement.ts` — places elements directly in DOM (1085 lines)\n- `src/state/hooks/useDragAndDrop.ts` — mermaid node drag system with `markDraggableElements`\n- `src/components/canvas/handlers/useDiagramCanvasEvents.ts` — routes mouse events to pan/drag handlers\n\n### SVG Structure\n```\n<svg style=\"transform: translate(panX, panY) scale(zoom)\">\n  <g data-diagram-content=\"true\">     ← stable group created by DiagramDisplay\n    <g id=\"flowchart-A-0\" transform=\"...\">  ← mermaid nodes (draggable)\n    <g data-custom-elements-layer class=\"custom-elements-layer\">  ← custom elements container\n      <g class=\"custom-icon-group\">   ← icons from useElementPlacement\n```\n\n### Playwright Cannot Reproduce\nSynthetic mouse events from Playwright don't trigger the same event chain as real user interactions. Specifically, `markDraggableElements` adds direct DOM `mousedown` handlers with `stopPropagation()` that behave differently with synthetic events.\n\n## TOOLS EXECUTED\n- Multiple `gh issue create/close` commands for issues #40-57\n- Multiple `npm run build && git push && wrangler deploy` cycles\n- Playwright MCP used extensivel